yle="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">minutage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> for local news has been cut </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">considerably</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Ofcom</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> has allowed ITV local news to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reduced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> by a third when the new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-year licenc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">es for ITV, ST</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">V, UTV and Channel 5 start in 2015. While the early evening news slots </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will still </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">last</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> half an hour, 10 minutes will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> include non-local content, taken from elsewhere. Regional lunchtime news bulletins will be reduced from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">six and a half</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> minutes to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">three </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">min</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">utes and late evening bulletins from 10 minutes to five minutes. The two daily regional news bulletins at weekends will be cut from 10 minutes to five minutes. </span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 22.11pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"